<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1289,1782]" pageId="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,457,1505,1530]" pageId="2">General distribution.</emphasis>
This species occurs widely in the Balkan Peninsula (
<collectingCountry box="[1111,1195,1506,1530]" name="Greece" pageId="2">Greece</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1212,1311,1505,1530]" name="Bulgaria" pageId="2">Bulgaria</collectingCountry>
, European 
<collectingCountry box="[151,236,1541,1566]" name="Turkey" pageId="2">Turkey</collectingCountry>
), including some major Greek islands; in the 
<collectingCountry box="[742,898,1541,1566]" name="Greece" pageId="2">Ionian islands</collectingCountry>
it was recorded in Lefkada (
<bibRefCitation author="Csabai, Z. &amp; Soos, N. &amp; Berchi, G. M. &amp; Cianferoni, F. &amp; Boda, P. &amp; Mora, A." box="[1216,1425,1541,1566]" pageId="2" pagination="51 - 69" refId="ref8620" refString="Csabai, Z., Soos, N., Berchi, G. M., Cianferoni, F., Boda, P. &amp; Mora, A. (2017) Aquatic and semiaquatic Heteroptera (Nepomorpha and Gerromorpha) fauna of Greek holiday islands (Rhodes, Crete and Corfu) with first records of three species from Europe and Greece. Zootaxa, 4231 (1), 51 - 69. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4231.1.3" type="journal article" year="2017">
Csabai 
<emphasis box="[1301,1357,1541,1565]" italics="true" pageId="2">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
). However, a more precise distribution of this species extending to Asia still needs to be defined. In addition to Balkans, this species was recorded from Asian 
<collectingCountry box="[699,779,1613,1638]" name="Turkey" pageId="2">Turkey</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[839,884,1614,1637]" name="Iran" pageId="2">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Samin, N. &amp; Sakenin, H. &amp; Linnavuori, R. &amp; Havaskary, M. &amp; Mohebbi, H. R." box="[901,1112,1613,1638]" pageId="2" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref10316" refString="Samin, N., Sakenin, H., Linnavuori, R., Havaskary, M. &amp; Mohebbi, H. R. (2011) A faunistic survey of Heteroptera (Insecta) from western Iran. Calodema, 146, 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="2011">
Samin 
<emphasis box="[984,1036,1613,1637]" italics="true" pageId="2">et al</emphasis>
. 2011
</bibRefCitation>
), but the latter record needs confirmation (
<bibRefCitation author="Aukema, B. &amp; Rieger, C. &amp; Rabitsch, W." box="[310,535,1649,1674]" pageId="2" refId="ref7736" refString="Aukema, B., Rieger, C. &amp; Rabitsch, W. (2013) Catalogue of the Heteroptera of the Palaearctic Region. Vol. 6. Supplement. The Netherlands Entomological Society, Ede, 629 pp." type="book" year="2013">
Aukema 
<emphasis box="[413,470,1649,1673]" italics="true" pageId="2">et al.</emphasis>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Csabai, Z. &amp; Soos, N. &amp; Berchi, G. M. &amp; Cianferoni, F. &amp; Boda, P. &amp; Mora, A." box="[547,754,1649,1674]" pageId="2" pagination="51 - 69" refId="ref8620" refString="Csabai, Z., Soos, N., Berchi, G. M., Cianferoni, F., Boda, P. &amp; Mora, A. (2017) Aquatic and semiaquatic Heteroptera (Nepomorpha and Gerromorpha) fauna of Greek holiday islands (Rhodes, Crete and Corfu) with first records of three species from Europe and Greece. Zootaxa, 4231 (1), 51 - 69. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4231.1.3" type="journal article" year="2017">
Csabai 
<emphasis box="[630,686,1649,1673]" italics="true" pageId="2">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
